  "title": "TabCommand CodeYam Redesign",
  "type": "feature",
  "userRequest": "pull from main for latest changes please",
  "description": "Re-skinned the entire TabCommand UI in the CodeYam dark/lime design language on top of the existing theme system: a CSS-token re-skin (dark default + matching light theme), the two-ring Browser Load gauge, a load-aware Triage panel with a Heaviest-Tabs rail, a new History page, an add-group color wheel, a Settings popover for the load thresholds, a built-in inline-SVG icon set (replacing @ant-design/icons), and the new branded favicon. The data model is unchanged — chrome storage, the chrome shim, drag-to-organize, search, and the per-tab/process load math stay authoritative; only markup, CSS, and organizational surfaces changed. Extracted pure helpers loadLevel and bucketByDay (tested) to de-duplicate the gauge/triage and history-bucketing logic.",
